Xpath  Axes are used to search for multiple nodes in the XML document from the current node context. These nodes are mainly used  when the web element is not 
identified with the help of id, name, className, linkText, partialLinkText, TagName, CSSSelector.

//a[contains(text(), 'LGB Forge Ltd.')]/parent::td/following-sibling::td

//a[contains(text(), 'LGB Forge Ltd.')]/ancestor::tr/descendant ::td

//a[contains(text(), 'LGB Forge Ltd.')]/ancestor::tr//td[3]

//a[contains(text(), 'LGB Forge Ltd.')]/ancestor::tr/child::td

/ => Immediate child to parent or ancestor

// => Any child

//a[contains(text(), 'LGB Forge Ltd.')]/ancestor::tr